To run in standalone mode:

1) Load the following modules:

module load contrib sutils

module load intel/18.0.5.274
module load impi/2018.0.4
module load netcdf/4.7.0

module use -a /scratch1/NCEPDEV/nems/emc.nemspara/soft/modulefiles
module load esmf/8.0.0

2) Link the input files from a Baseline area:
cd DATM_INPUT
ln -s /scratch1/NCEPDEV/nems/emc.nemspara/RT/DATM-MOM6-CICE5/update-20200127/DATM/CFSR/201110/cfsr* .
ln -s /scratch1/NCEPDEV/nems/emc.nemspara/RT/DATM-MOM6-CICE5/update-20200127/DATM/GEFS/201110/gefs* .
ln -s /scratch1/NCEPDEV/nems/emc.nemspara/RT/DATM-MOM6-CICE5/update-20200127/DATM/cfsr.SCRIP.nc .
ln -s /scratch1/NCEPDEV/nems/emc.nemspara/RT/DATM-MOM6-CICE5/update-20200127/DATM/gefs.SCRIP.nc .

3) Link the configuration files:
ln -s model_configure.IN model_configure
ln -s datm_data_table.IN datm_data_table
==> edit the model_configure for either cfsr or gefs input


4) Compile : type "make"

5) Run:

in serial mode: ./esmApp 
in parallel mode: launch an interactive job
salloc --x11=first -q debug -t 0:30:00 --nodes=4 -A marine-cpu

wait until the job launches and then
srun --nodes=4 ./esmApp
